source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/spanish-style-chorizo-rice-668428aba0dfed75d9dfb361
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an
> ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%grams} and onion and fry until the chorizo
starts to brown and the onion has softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir frequently and
adjust the heat if necessary.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled @water for the stock{500%milliliter} into a #measuring jug{}.

Once the onion has softened, add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @risotto rice{175%grams} to the pan. Stir and cook until the edges of
the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour in the boiled water and @chicken stock paste{15%grams}. Stir well to
combine and bring back to the boil, then pop a lid on the pan (or cover with
#foil{}).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water
has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and cut the @lemon{1}(zested and cut into wedges) into wedges.

When everything's ready, remove the rice from the oven and stir in the
@peas{120%grams}.

Squeeze in some lemon juice from a lemon wedge and season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}. Stir in the @butter{20%grams} until melted.

Taste and add more salt, pepper and lemon juice if needed.

Spoon the rice onto your plates. Sprinkle over the lemon zest to finish.

Serve with a lemon wedge alongside.

Enjoy!